CBOT raises September corn margins . The Chicago Board of Trade said it raised the minimum initial margin requirement to trade September corn futures to $ 1 , 148 per contract from $ 810 , effective with the overnight Project A trading session on Wednesday , August 28 . Hedge and maintenance margins were raised to $ 850 per contract from $ 600 . Friday is first notice day for deliveries against the September CBOT grain contracts , including corn . But Thursday is first position day , when September contracts begin trading without daily limits , traders said . ( Chicago newsdesk 312 408 8720 ) 
